# Section: \hfill{}$\geqq$04.01
# Leviticus 04:01
Yahweh spoke to Moses,
saying,
# Leviticus 04:02
{
  Speak to the children of Israel,
  saying,
  {
    >>>>If anyone sins unintentionally,
    in any of the things
      which Yahweh has commanded not to be done,
    and does any one of them,
    # Leviticus 04:03
    if the anointed priest sins
      so as to bring guilt on the people,
    then let him offer
    for his sin which he has sinned
    a young bull without defect
    to Yahweh
    for a >>sin offering<<.
  }
}

# Section: \hfill{}$\geqq$04.04
{
  {
    # Leviticus 04:04
    He shall bring the bull
    to the door of the Tent of Meeting
    before Yahweh;
    and he shall lay his hand on the head of the bull,
    and kill the bull before Yahweh.

    # Leviticus 04:05
    The anointed priest shall take some of the blood of the bull,
    and bring it to the Tent of Meeting.

    # Leviticus 04:06
    The priest shall dip his finger in the blood,
    and sprinkle some of the blood seven times before Yahweh,
    before the veil of the sanctuary.

    # Leviticus 04:07
    The priest shall put some of the blood
    on the horns of the altar of sweet incense
    before Yahweh,
    which is in the Tent of Meeting;
    and he shall pour out
    the rest of the blood of the bull
    at the base of the altar of >>burnt offering<<,
    which is at the door of the Tent of Meeting.
  }
}

# Section: \hfill{}$\geqq$04.08
{
  {
    # Leviticus 04:08
    He shall take all the fat
    of the bull of the >>sin offering<< from it:
    the fat that covers the innards,
    and all the fat that is on the innards,
    # Leviticus 04:09
    and the two kidneys,
    and the fat that is on them,
    which is by the loins,
    and the cover on the liver,
    with the kidneys,
    he shall remove,
    # Leviticus 04:10
    as it is removed from the bull
    of the sacrifice of >>peace offerings<<.

    The priest shall burn them on the altar of >>burnt offering<<.

    # Leviticus 04:11
    He shall carry the bull's skin,
    all its meat,
    with its head,
    and with its legs,
    its innards,
    and its dung ---
    # Leviticus 04:12
    all the rest of the bull ---
    outside of the camp
    to a clean place where the ashes are poured out,
    and burn it on wood with fire.

    It shall be burned where the ashes are poured out.
  }
}

